    "# Problem 18: The Smart Container Terminal Integration Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "## Tier 6: The Autonomous & Self-Optimizing Ecosystem (Distributed Intelligence)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Problem Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "In previous tiers, we developed optimization approaches ranging from mathematical programming to integrated digital twins. **Tier 6 introduces the Autonomous & Self-Optimizing Ecosystem** that transforms yard crane scheduling from centralized control to emergent optimization through intelligent multi-agent collaboration. Each crane operates as an autonomous agent capable of negotiating job assignments, coordinating movements, and adapting to dynamic conditions without central supervision.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Autonomous Ecosystem vs Centralized Control?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Advantages of Autonomous Ecosystem:**\n",
    "1. **Distributed Intelligence**: No single point of failure\n",
    "2. **Emergent Behavior**: Complex coordination emerges from simple agent rules\n",
    "3. **Adaptability**: System adapts to local conditions in real-time\n",
    "4. **Scalability**: Easy to add/remove agents without system redesign\n",
    "5. **Resilience**: System continues operating even if some agents fail\n",
    "\n",
    "**Disadvantages:**\n",
    "1. **Coordination Complexity**: Requires sophisticated communication protocols\n",
    "2. **Convergence Guarantees**: May not always reach global optimum\n",
    "3. **Implementation Complexity**: More complex to design and debug\n",
    "4. **Performance Variability**: Results may vary between runs\n",
    "\n",
    "### Autonomous Ecosystem Components:\n",
    "1. **Intelligent Agents**: Autonomous crane agents with decision-making capabilities\n",
    "2. **Communication Protocols**: Message passing and negotiation mechanisms\n",
    "3. **Game Theory Foundation**: Strategic interaction and equilibrium concepts\n",
    "4. **Learning Mechanisms**: Adaptation and improvement over time\n",
    "5. **Emergent Behaviors**: Specialization and role development"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import required packages\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n",
    "from typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Optional, Any\n",
    "import time\n",
    "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n",
    "import random\n",
    "from collections import defaultdict, deque\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "from enum import Enum\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set visualization style\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ All packages imported successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Autonomous Agent Data Structures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AgentRole(Enum):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Enumeration of possible agent roles\"\"\"\n",
    "    GENERALIST = \"generalist\"\n",
    "    HIGH_PRIORITY_SPECIALIST = \"high_priority_specialist\"\n",
    "    BULK_HANDLER = \"bulk_handler\"\n",
    "    EMERGENCY_RESPONDER = \"emergency_responder\"\n",
    "    SYSTEM_OPTIMIZER = \"system_optimizer\"\n",
    "\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class Message:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Communication message between agents\"\"\"\n",
    "    sender_id: str\n",
    "    receiver_id: str\n",
    "    message_type: str  # 'bid', 'award', 'request', 'inform', 'negotiate'\n",
    "    content: Dict[str, Any]\n",
    "    timestamp: datetime\n",
    "    priority: int = 1  # 1=low, 2=medium, 3=high\n",
    "\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class Bid:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Bid for a job assignment\"\"\"\n",
    "    agent_id: str\n",
    "    job_id: str\n",
    "    cost: float  # Estimated completion cost\n",
    "    confidence: float  # Confidence in successful completion (0-1)\n",
    "    availability_time: int  # Time until agent is available\n",
    "    specialization_bonus: float  # Bonus for agent's specialization\n",
    "\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class UtilityFunction:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Utility function for agent decision making\"\"\"\n",
    "    weight_cost: float = 0.4  # Weight for cost minimization\n",
    "    weight_time: float = 0.3  # Weight for time minimization\n",
    "    weight_specialization: float = 0.2  # Weight for specialization alignment\n",
    "    weight_workload_balance: float = 0.1  # Weight for workload balance\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def calculate_utility(self, bid: Bid, agent_workload: float) -> float:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Calculate utility for a bid\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Normalize components\n",
    "        normalized_cost = 1.0 / (1.0 + bid.cost)  # Lower cost = higher utility\n",
    "        normalized_time = 1.0 / (1.0 + bid.availability_time)  # Sooner = higher utility\n",
    "        specialization_utility = bid.specialization_bonus\n",
    "        workload_utility = 1.0 - agent_workload  # Lower workload = higher utility\n",
    "        \n",
    "        utility = (self.weight_cost * normalized_cost +\n",
    "                  self.weight_time * normalized_time +\n",
    "                  self.weight_specialization * specialization_utility +\n",
    "                  self.weight_workload_balance * workload_utility)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return utility"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class CraneAgent:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Autonomous crane agent\"\"\"\n",
    "    agent_id: str\n",
    "    crane_id: int\n",
    "    position: Tuple[float, float]\n",
    "    capacity: float\n",
    "    "speed: float\n",
    "    "status: str = 'idle'\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Agent properties\n",
    "    role: AgentRole = AgentRole.GENERALIST\n",
    "    "utility_function: UtilityFunction = field(default_factory=UtilityFunction)\n",
    "    "experience_level: float = 0.5  # 0-1, increases with successful jobs\n",
    "    "specialization_score: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\n",
    "        'high_priority': 0.2,\n",
    "        'bulk': 0.2,\n",
    "        'emergency': 0.2,\n",
    "        'standard': 0.2\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Agent state\n",
    "    "current_job: Optional[str] = None\n",
    "    "job_history: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n",
    "    "workload: float = 0.0  # Current workload (0-1)\n",
    "    "performance_metrics: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=dict)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Communication\n",
    "    "message_queue: List[Message] = field(default_factory=list)\n",
    "    "neighbors: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)  # Connected agents\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Learning\n",
    "    "success_rate: float = 0.8\n",
    "    "adaptation_rate: float = 0.1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Autonomous agent data structures defined!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Autonomous Agent Implementation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AutonomousCraneAgent:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Intelligent autonomous crane agent\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, agent_id: str, crane_id: int, position: Tuple[float, float], \n",
    "                 capacity: float, speed: float):\n",
    "        self.agent = CraneAgent(\n",
    "            agent_id=agent_id,\n",
    "            crane_id=crane_id,\n",
    "            position=position,\n",
    "            capacity=capacity,\n",
    "            speed=speed\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Initialize agent capabilities\n",
    "        self._initialize_capabilities()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _initialize_capabilities(self):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Initialize agent capabilities and preferences\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Random initial specialization tendencies\n",
    "        specializations = ['high_priority', 'bulk', 'emergency', 'standard']\n",
    "        total = 0.0\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for spec in specializations:\n",
    "            value = np.random.uniform(0.1, 0.4)\n",
    "            self.agent.specialization_score[spec] = value\n",
    "            total += value\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Normalize to sum to 1.0\n",
    "        for spec in specializations:\n",
    "            self.agent.specialization_score[spec] /= total\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Autonomous Crane Agent class defined!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Multi-Agent Coordination System"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class MultiAgentCoordinationSystem:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Multi-agent coordination system with auction-based job allocation\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, num_agents: int):\n",
    "        self.num_agents = num_agents\n",
    "        self.agents: Dict[str, AutonomousCraneAgent] = {}\n",
    "        self.job_queue: List[Job] = []\n",
    "        self.completed_jobs: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []\n",
    "        self.current_time = datetime.now()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # System metrics\n",
    "        self.coordination_overhead = 0.0\n",
    "        self.nash_equilibrium_achieved = False\n",
    "        self.emergent_behaviors = []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Initialize agents\n",
    "        self._initialize_agents()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _initialize_agents(self):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Initialize autonomous crane agents\"\"\"\n",
    "        print(f\"🤖 Initializing {self.num_agents} autonomous crane agents...\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for i in range(self.num_agents):\n",
    "            agent_id = f\"agent_{i+1}\"\n",
    "            crane_id = i + 1\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Random initial positions\n",
    "            position = (np.random.uniform(0, 1000), np.random.uniform(0, 500))\n",
    "            capacity = np.random.uniform(40, 60)  # 40-60 tons\n",
    "            speed = np.random.uniform(50, 100)  # 50-100 m/min\n",
    "            \n",
    "            agent = AutonomousCraneAgent(agent_id, crane_id, position, capacity, speed)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Set up neighbor connections (small-world network)\n",
    "            self._setup_agent_neighbors(agent)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            self.agents[agent_id] = agent\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"✅ Initialized {len(self.agents)} agents with neighbor connections\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _setup_agent_neighbors(self, agent: AutonomousCraneAgent):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Set up neighbor connections for agent\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Connect to 2-4 random neighbors\n",
    "        num_neighbors = np.random.randint(2, 5)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for i in range(num_neighbors):\n",
    "            neighbor_id = f\"agent_{np.random.randint(1, self.num_agents + 1)}\"\n",
    "            if neighbor_id != agent.agent.agent_id and neighbor_id not in agent.agent.neighbors:\n",
    "                agent.agent.neighbors.append(neighbor_id)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Multi-Agent Coordination System defined!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
